en_853566_0	Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa has instructed the officials to implement a special programme to evacuate people from the areas affected by the inclement weather.
en_853566_1	A discussion was held between the Premier and the officials.
en_853566_2	The people from nine districts have been affected by the extreme weather.
en_853566_3	Discussions were held regarding the management of displaced persons and taking adequate precautions to prevent such disaster in the future.
en_853566_4	The Prime Minister instructed the officials to provide cooked meals and sanitation to the displaced persons without delay.
en_853566_5	The victims will also be handed over dry rations.
en_853566_6	The Prime Minister instructed the officials to pay special attention to the victimized children.
en_853566_7	Ministers, MPs and the Commanders of the tri-forces and the IGP were present at the discussion.
